# Build a Virtual Private Cloud (Amazon VPC)

## Project Overview

In this project, I designed and deployed a custom Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) to create an isolated networking environment within AWS. The objective was to understand the foundational networking components that support secure and scalable cloud infrastructure.

The implementation included creating a custom VPC, configuring a public subnet, assigning an IPv4 CIDR block, attaching an Internet Gateway, and enabling internet connectivity for resources launched inside the subnet.

This project reinforces core networking concepts that every Cloud Engineer and Solutions Architect relies on when designing production AWS environments.

