# Implementation Steps

## 1. Created a Custom VPC

Created a new Amazon VPC and assigned an IPv4 CIDR block to define the private address space for the environment.

---

## 2. Configured a Public Subnet

Created a subnet within the VPC and enabled Auto-Assign Public IPv4 Address so that newly launched EC2 instances automatically receive public IP addresses.

---

## 3. Attached an Internet Gateway

Provisioned and attached an Internet Gateway (IGW) to provide internet access for resources inside the VPC.

---

## 4. Configured Routing

Configured routing to direct internet-bound traffic (0.0.0.0/0) through the Internet Gateway, allowing public subnet resources to communicate externally.

---

## 5. Validated Connectivity

Verified that the networking configuration successfully allowed internet access through the configured public subnet.

